{"questionId":"1fe32f7d","correctAnswer":"51","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up the discriminant condition","content":"$-x^2+bx-676=0$ has $a=-1$, $c=-676$. No real solutions requires $\\Delta&lt;0$:<br/>$$b^2-4(-1)(-676)=b^2-2704&lt;0$$"},{"title":"Solve the inequality","content":"$$b^2&lt;2704 \\Rightarrow b&lt;\\sqrt{2704}=52$$"},{"title":"Find the greatest positive integer","content":"$b$ must be a positive integer less than $52$, so $b=51$. The answer is <strong>51</strong>."}]}